{
  "_comment": "Symbolic asset keys -> file paths. Apps and UI modules NEVER hardcode a raw path like 'assets/icons/about.png'. They ask AssetManager.getAsset('icon.about') (or emit asset:get) and receive whatever this file currently points to. Swapping an icon, wallpaper, or sound later is a one-line change here, not a hunt through every app file. Categories below (icons/wallpapers/images/sounds/documents) exist purely for human readability when editing this file -- AssetManager flattens them into one lookup map internally, so keys must be unique across the whole file, not just within a category.",

